  "exec_summary": "The European Banking Authority has issued an email alert as of July 1, 2026, however the most significant EU regulatory development this week is the implementation of the Markets in Crypto-Assets regulation, known as MiCA, which has taken effect and is being closely monitored by regulators such as the Bank of Latvia, which has granted a MiCA license to Backpack. Meanwhile, EagleBank is paying over $9.7 million in relation to a money laundering probe, highlighting the importance of anti-money laundering compliance. The MiCA regulation is having a significant impact on the crypto industry in Europe, with only 244 licenses granted ahead of the deadline.",
